{"word":"μαινάς","slug":"μαινάς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>μαινάς</b></el> <el>(μαινάς, άδος,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:μαίνομαι'><el>μαίνομαι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>raving, frantic</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>as <a href='S:Substantive'>Subst.</a> <i>a mad woman</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>: <a href='S:especially'>esp.</a> <i>a Bacchante, Bacchanal, Maenad</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; of the Furies, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; of Cassandra, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>causing madness</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}